{"id": "EUVD-2022-55588", "enisaUuid": "fbe72ba9-b551-389d-979a-c7d6c7111c26", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nmmc: rtsx_pci: fix return value check of mmc_add_host()\n\nmmc_add_host() may return error, if we ignore its return value, the memory\nthat allocated in mmc_alloc_host() will be leaked and it will lead a kernel\ncrash because of deleting not added device in the remove path.\n\nSo fix this by checking the return value and calling mmc_free_host() in the\nerror path, beside, runtime PM also needs be disabled.", "datePublished": "2025-09-15T15:31:25", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-03T18:30:19", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/30dc645461dfc63e52b3af8ee4a98e17bf14bacf", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/5cd4e04eccaec140da6fa04db056a76282ee6852", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ffa9b2a79e3e959683efbad3f6db937eca9d38f5", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/0c87db77423a282b3b38b8a6daf057b822680516", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50267"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50267"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "004fa2eb-092a-39c1-95d7-f99d7fb62db1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "ff984e57d36e8ac468849a144a36f1c11f88b61c <0c87db77423a282b3b38b8a6daf057b822680516"}, {"id": "0fb67608-06dc-3cc4-8ec9-fc6c61b2bde8", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.0.16"}, {"id": "15e699c6-14c1-32db-86ba-43993061560e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "3.8"}, {"id": "21b43589-d3e2-3221-ac87-98ad36724924", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.86"}, {"id": "2a96d6da-6746-3b53-b1fa-0951d4fae3a3", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "ff984e57d36e8ac468849a144a36f1c11f88b61c <ffa9b2a79e3e959683efbad3f6db937eca9d38f5"}, {"id": "2d233001-5b4c-3a38-bca7-5f3c31dd4e62", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "7bd7645c-ca9c-3d77-bc1a-79eb6d4e5b86", "product": {"na